@startuml
title Viaverse Capability — Package / Component Diagram

package "apps/mobile-kmp" {
  component "ModeSwitcher UI" as ModeUi
  component "Profile screen" as ProfileUi
}

component "API Gateway / App BFF\nAccount summary\nMode switch request" as BFF
component "identity-service\nAccountCapability\nSession mode claim\nCapability policy" as Identity
component "business-service / marketplace boundary\nBusinessProfile\nBusinessTeamMember\nBusiness verification" as Business
component "admin-bff\nCapability operations\nSuspension/revoke\nAudit reason" as Admin
database "PostgreSQL\naccounts\naccount_capabilities\nbusiness_profiles\nteam_members" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nCapabilityEnabled\nCapabilitySuspended\nActiveModeChanged" as Kafka

ModeUi --> BFF : REST
ProfileUi --> BFF : REST
BFF --> Identity : REST/gRPC
Identity --> Business : business checks
Admin --> Identity : admin commands
Identity --> DB : JPA
Business --> DB : JPA
Identity --> Kafka : outbox
Kafka ..> BFF : projection / refresh summary

note bottom
Mode switching is a client UX action,
but eligibility is always decided by backend capability policies.
end note
@enduml
